<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-10T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-10T01:00:00-05:00" n="653" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121/41: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Standley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-10T09:00:00+03:00">June 10,
                                    1943—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3; 40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>639. Department’s 263, April 28, 7 p.m.<note n="18" xml:id="d653fn18">Not
                                printed. Mrs. Nerma Oggins of New York City bad deposited the sum of
                                $400 towards the expense of the return of her husband. The
                                Department of State had authorized on April 20, 1943, the issuance
                                of a passport valid only for return to the United States.
                                (361.1121/40a)</note> and 269, April 30,<note n="19" xml:id="d653fn19">Not printed.</note> re Isaiah Oggins. Embassy has
                            been refused permission to see Oggins again and is informed that the
                            competent Soviet authorities find it impossible to reconsider his case.
                            Funds released for, refund depositor.<note n="20" xml:id="d653fn20">The
                                deposited money was returned to Mrs. Oggins on June 22, 1943.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>